 circle (Ø 28 cm). Place it on prepared baking tray and spread the filling over the dough, leaving a 2 cm border."},{"content":"Roll the second piece of dough into a circle (Ø 28 cm), place it over the filling and press the edges together, then fold edges over forming a firm seal."},{"content":"Whisk egg yolk with water using a fork and brush over surface of bread. Use a sharp knife to make small slits over top of bread and bake for 20-25 minutes (200°C) until golden. Serve warm, garnished with reserved Parmesan cheese-parsley mixture."}],"hintsAndTricks":["This bread is delicious warm and fresh from the oven, while the cheese is still soft.","To reheat the bread, simply wrap in greaseproof paper or baking paper, and warm in the oven 140°C for 10 minutes.","The combination of Parmesan and mozzarella keeps the cheese soft and gooey, with the full flavour from the Parmesan.","Any kind of brewed beer would go well with this satisfying bread."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","45m","12 slices"]}